co-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527353\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 18, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104evw1665702995189.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/evw1665702995189.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/evw1665702995189.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"evw1665702995189\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Deploying Server Pages and Web Services on iSeries\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">For Uniface on the iSeries to run Uniface dynamic and static server pages and web services, you need to move the UAR containing the server pages or Web services and their associated files and signatures onto your iSeries, and set the appropriate assignment file settings.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"evw1665702995189__context_w1819ab1b5b1_w1820ab1b5_w1821ab1\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"evw1665702995189__note_w1822ab1b5b1b1_w1823ab1b5b1_w1824ab1b5_w1825ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> For purposes of\n            illustration in the following procedure, we are creating a test service called\n               <span class=\"ph filepath\">websrv.svc</span>, deploying it on the iSeries, and running it as a web\n            service. The service will be called from a form running in the Uniface IDE on a Windows\n            client.</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step\" id=\"evw1665702995189__li_d29198e1_d29199e1_d29200e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"als1665702995258.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/als1665702995258.html\" title=\"To be able to deploy Uniface web applications on the iSeries, you must configure the Uniface Web Application Server so that it can correctly locate and run web components. To do so, you need to ensure that assignment files of the Uniface Router, Uniface Server, and client assignment file match the Web Application Server defined in the web.xml file.\">Configure the Uniface Web Application Server on iSeries</a>\n</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"evw1665702995189__li_d29201e1_d29202e1_d29203e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qmw1665702995400.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qmw1665702995400.html\" title=\"For testing purposes, create a test service that can be used as a web service on iSeries, and a form that can call the service.\">Create and Run a Test Service on iSeries</a>\n</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"evw1665702995189__li_d29204e1_d29205e1_d29206e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cul1665702995473.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cul1665702995473.html\" title=\"After you have confirmed that the test service websrv.svc runs correctly, you can deploy it as a web service. To do so, you need to generate a WSDL file that describes the interface to web service clients that wish to invoke the service, and then configure the WRD to use this file.\">Run the Service as a Web Service</a>\n</span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/snh1704692180687.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Static Server Pages</a><p>Static Server Page (USP) components generate a complete web page every time they are activated. This makes them useful for relatively static web pages or a thin-client architecture in which all processing is done on the server. They can also be used for RESTful applications or file upload functionality.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lmy1665702545752.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Web Services</a><p>A web service is software that makes its functionality available over the Internet.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527353\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527353\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Deploying Server Pages and Web Services on iSeries Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 18, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Deploying Server Pages and Web Services on iSeries For Uniface on the iSeries to run Uniface dynamic and static server pages and web services, you need to move the UAR containing the server pages or Web services and their associated files and signatures onto your iSeries, and set the appropriate assignment file settings. Note: For purposes of illustration in the following procedure, we are creating a test service called websrv.svc , deploying it on the iSeries, and running it as a web service. The service will be called from a form running in the Uniface IDE on a Windows client. Configure the Uniface Web Application Server on iSeries Create and Run a Test Service on iSeries Run the Service as a Web Service Related Links Static Server Pages Static Server Page (USP) components generate a complete web page every time they are activated. This makes them useful for relatively static web pages or a thin-client architecture in which all processing is done on the server. They can also be used for RESTful applications or file upload functionality. Web Services A web service is software that makes its functionality available over the Internet. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}